result.execSummary:
The defendant Trevor K. Munkelwitz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Trevor K. Munkelwitz is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Trevor K. Munkelwitz was found guilty of Possess w/ Intent-THC(>200-1000g), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)2.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Froelich - plea to Ct. 1, S/W, 3 yrs probation, conditional jail time 6 to 7 months, concurrent with LaCrosse County Case 09CF303, dismiss Ct 2.   Nelson in agrdement. Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.    Constitutional rights explained to defendant.    Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights.    DEF PLEADS GUILTY to Count 1.  Facts are correct.    COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS.    The court finds the defendant guilty of Count 1 and adjudicates defendant guilty of Count 1.  Court dismisses Count 2.  Court Orders:  S/W, 3 years probation, conditional jail time of 6 months, sentence  to run concurrent with La Crosse County Case, costs and DNA surcharge - $515.00.    Appeal rights are given to the defendant.

10:47 a.m.  Defendant Trevor K. Munkelwitz in court with attorney Liesl E. Nelson.  Defendant Trevor K. Munkelwitz in custody.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Waiver of plea hearing and then going to plea.    Judge exams the defendant re the waiver of preliminary hearing.  Court finds defendant freely, intelligently, knowingly, and understandingly made and waives constitutional right to a preliminary hearing.    The court finds probable cause and binds defendant over for further proceedings. Froelich files information; Def has a copy.
